cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.HC. 

The paper involves the use of deep learning algorithms to analyze medical images, specifically retinal fundus images, to predict refractive error. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of attention maps and the identification of important features suggest the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also has implications for healthcare (cs.MED) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it discusses the potential use of mobile phones and inexpensive attachments for obtaining retinal fundus photos in regions where autorefractors may not be readily available.
